Package: econometricstoolbox
Type: Package
Title: Deterministic Backend for Manifest-Driven Panel Regression
Version: 0.1.2
Date: 2026-05-25
Authors@R: person("Yeonchan", "Lee", email = "nanyeon99@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A fail-closed R backend for panel fixed-effects regression
    invoked by an external empirical execution layer. The package reads a
    YAML call manifest, validates it strictly, runs fixest::feols exactly
    as declared, and emits a result manifest with package versions, row
    counts, and four SHA-256 drift signatures. Identical inputs produce
    byte-identical coefficient output.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
